Durban - A  94-year-old man was allegedly strangled to death in his home in Hayfields, Pietermaritzburg on Wednesday morning in an apparent house robbery. ER24 spokesperson, Russel Meiring, said paramedics arrived on the scene shortly before 8am and found the man lying in a pool of blood in one of the rooms. "Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for the man and he was declared dead." Police spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, said the man's body was found with strangulation marks around his neck. "A  white VW Polo was taken from the garage and no other items were stolen." Zwane said Alexandra Road SAPS were investigating a case of house robbery and murder. No arrests had been made. A week ago, Christopher Munro Biggs, 73, was beaten to death in an alleged robbery at his home in Manor Gardens, Durban. He was allegedly found bound with rope and gagged in his bedroom. It is believed the man had been dead for two days. A case of murder was opened at Mayville police station for investigation. No arrests had been made. POST